\f0\b\fs50 \cf0 Chocolate Chip Cookies
\b0\fs24 \

\fs30 Makes about 25 cookies\
\
INGREDIENTS
\fs44 \
2 1/2 c. all-purpose flour\
1 t. baking soda\
1 t. salt\
2 sticks unsalted butter, at room temperature\
1 c. packed light brown sugar\
1/2 c. granulated sugar\
1 tablespoon vanilla extract\
1 large egg plus 1 egg yolk\
1 c. M&M's\
3 ounces bittersweet chocolate, chopped\
1/2 c.  toffee pieces\
3/4 c. peanut butter chips\
\

\fs30 DIRECTIONS
\fs44 \
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.\
Whisk flour, baking soda and salt in a bowl.\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\ri540\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\cf0 In a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, cream the butter, brown sugar \
and granulated sugar on low speed until incorporated, then increase to high\
speed and beat until light and fluffy.\
Add the salt, vanilla, whole egg and egg yolk to the mixer; beat until throughly\
combined.  Add the M&M's and beat a few seconds.\
Gradually add the flour mixture, mixing on low speed until just combined.\
Mix in the bittersweet chocolate, toffee pieces and peanut butter chips.\
Roll heaping tablespoonfuls of dough into balls, about 2 inches apart.  Slightly flatted\
each ball.\
Bake the cookies until the edges are golden brown and the centers are no longer wet, 11 to 13 minutes.\
